WEBVTT

00:01.280 --> 00:04.204
[slow-tempo guitar plays]

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:15.560 --> 00:17.801
[Tommy] Come on, bud.
You got to get up, get dressed.

00:21.920 --> 00:23.410
[sighs]

00:27.400 --> 00:29.641
Yeah, I, uh,
I had trouble getting out of bed, too,

00:29.720 --> 00:32.564
this morning, thinking about tomorrow.

00:35.600 --> 00:36.681
You know what I was thinking?

00:38.480 --> 00:40.403
I was thinking maybe we could, uh...

00:41.800 --> 00:43.165
I don't know, make her something.

00:44.720 --> 00:49.408
You know? Like a-- like a nice card, or...
even a cake.

00:53.640 --> 00:54.880
We'll get through it.

00:56.760 --> 01:00.207
Just like the whole year,
you and me, okay?

01:03.600 --> 01:05.203
[upbeat music plays]

01:05.280 --> 01:06.725
All right, people.

01:06.800 --> 01:09.167
The clock is our bitch today, okay?

01:09.840 --> 01:11.080
Let me taste that.

01:12.000 --> 01:13.968
Oh, my God. I love it!

01:14.080 --> 01:16.401
No, no! Not now, Chef! I'm mid-whisk!

01:16.480 --> 01:18.642
Looking good, Val.
Hey, Habib. Come on.

01:18.720 --> 01:20.802
Perfect cubes. I want perfect cubes.

01:20.880 --> 01:22.723
I got your cubes right here, Chef.

01:22.800 --> 01:24.643
Hey, what's the haps, T.J.?

01:28.320 --> 01:29.765
[Dion]
Hey, dude. You all right?

01:31.240 --> 01:33.607
How about tomorrow,
I show you how to bake a cake?

01:33.800 --> 01:34.847
Hmm?

01:35.080 --> 01:37.447
- Have a think about it, okay?
- Do you have a finalized menu?

01:37.520 --> 01:38.885
You know, the one I asked for yesterday

01:38.960 --> 01:41.247
and the day before yesterday,
and pretty much every day this week?

01:41.320 --> 01:42.481
Yeah, sorry. I've been kind of busy

01:42.560 --> 01:44.688
making up for the week that
that idiot chef wasted

01:44.760 --> 01:47.809
turning my restaurant
into a pile of deep-fried shit.

01:47.920 --> 01:50.161
I need to get the menu to the printer.

01:50.240 --> 01:52.004
Patience, chica, all right?

01:52.120 --> 01:53.610
Wh-- What's the Spanish word
for "patience?"

01:54.120 --> 01:56.930
[Speaking Spanish]

01:57.200 --> 01:59.009
All right, but that's more than one word.

02:01.240 --> 02:03.163
[Mose] Tommy! Tommy.

02:03.240 --> 02:04.765
For the outside sign.

02:05.280 --> 02:07.487
You wouldn't believe
the things people throw away.

02:07.560 --> 02:10.609
- Nice, Mose.
- I have a lead on a spectacular

02:10.759 --> 02:12.125
Can't wait to see it.

02:16.360 --> 02:17.361
Oof.

02:18.360 --> 02:21.682
- Such waste!
- One of Chef Kevin's uninspired choices.

02:21.760 --> 02:24.240
- Good riddance.
- Maybe some people would like it.

02:24.320 --> 02:25.765
Believe me, if we serve this crap,

02:25.840 --> 02:28.525
the state will revoke our liquor license.
[chuckles]

02:31.800 --> 02:32.961
What?

02:33.640 --> 02:34.880
[mid-tempo guitar plays]

02:35.680 --> 02:37.887
Please tell me we have a liquor license.

02:38.200 --> 02:39.201
[Tommy] Pilar.

02:39.280 --> 02:41.203
I sent the application with the check.

02:41.280 --> 02:43.328
I forgot to follow up.
It's been crazy here.

02:47.960 --> 02:49.689
Okay, when did you send the check?

02:49.760 --> 02:50.886
Last week.

02:51.640 --> 02:54.769
Pilar, it could take months
to get a liquor license!

02:54.840 --> 02:56.330
We-- We open in six days.

02:56.400 --> 02:58.641
I'm so sorry. I feel awful.

02:59.160 --> 03:00.286
[cellphone vibrates]

03:02.480 --> 03:03.481
Oh!

03:04.000 --> 03:05.126
Oh, thank God.

03:05.480 --> 03:07.369
[sniffs] My sister woke up.

03:08.200 --> 03:09.531
L-- I should see her.

03:09.600 --> 03:11.045
I'm so happy!

03:11.440 --> 03:13.488
I mean, I still feel awful, but--

03:14.000 --> 03:16.367
Oh, I know a guy
in the restaurant business

03:16.440 --> 03:17.441
that might help out.

03:17.520 --> 03:18.885
- L-- I'll make a call.
- No.

03:18.960 --> 03:20.405
You know what? Don't call anyone.

03:20.480 --> 03:22.926
Don't-- don't do anything.
You should go see your sister.

03:23.000 --> 03:24.047
It's more important.

03:24.120 --> 03:25.326
- Go.
- But the liquor license--

03:25.400 --> 03:26.845
I'll handle it. Go.

03:28.520 --> 03:29.521
[sighs]

03:35.280 --> 03:36.611
Hey. We got an issue.

03:36.680 --> 03:37.920
All right, guys.
Guys, hold your thoughts.

03:38.000 --> 03:41.288
Hold your thoughts. I want to know
what Mr. Moran thinks first.

03:41.360 --> 03:43.681
- Dion, I-- I need--
- Come on. Taste it.

03:46.160 --> 03:47.366
[Dion] A little bit of sauce.

03:47.520 --> 03:48.931
Food. Fork.

03:49.520 --> 03:50.567
Thoughts.

03:52.800 --> 03:54.006
It's good.

03:54.280 --> 03:55.486
What-- that's it?

03:55.640 --> 03:57.688
It's amazing, okay? It's erection-worthy.

03:58.120 --> 03:59.121
All right, come on, man.

03:59.240 --> 04:01.083
Don't-- Don't tell me what you think
I want to hear, all right?

04:01.160 --> 04:02.764
Tell me what I need to know.

04:02.840 --> 04:05.161
Look,
Rie always told me what I needed to know.

04:05.240 --> 04:07.129
Yeah, I need you to be
that voice for me, man.

04:07.200 --> 04:08.247
Here's what you need to know.

04:08.320 --> 04:10.288
You need to finalize our fantastic menu

04:10.360 --> 04:12.886
so the rest of us can do our jobs, okay?

04:15.960 --> 04:18.007
T., T., T., T.!
T.

04:19.399 --> 04:20.401
Hey.

04:20.959 --> 04:21.961
[whispers] Is this about tomorrow?

04:22.040 --> 04:23.041
No.

04:26.440 --> 04:27.487
Maybe.

04:29.800 --> 04:30.847
Yeah.

04:31.320 --> 04:32.970
Whatever you need, huh?

04:33.320 --> 04:34.367
You know that, right?

04:34.960 --> 04:37.088
- Yeah, thanks.
- All right.

04:45.680 --> 04:46.886
Everything okay?

04:47.360 --> 04:48.407
Yeah, yeah.

04:48.520 --> 04:49.601
It's, uh...

04:50.560 --> 04:52.005
it's Rie's birthday tomorrow.

04:54.280 --> 04:56.408
Anyway, look, uh, come on, man.
Tell me.

04:56.960 --> 04:58.564
Do I need a different protein?

04:58.880 --> 05:00.370
- You need a different protein.
- You need a different protein.

05:00.440 --> 05:01.805
- You need a different protein.

05:01.880 --> 05:04.724
All right, I'm thinking... I'm thinking...

05:05.560 --> 05:08.484
Oh. Oh, I'm thinking...

05:08.560 --> 05:10.085
What do you got?

05:10.400 --> 05:11.845
- I'm thinking langoustines, huh?
- Perfect!

05:12.280 --> 05:13.930
- Yeah.
- [Val] Yes!

05:14.320 --> 05:15.606
[door opens]

05:19.520 --> 05:22.126
Our agreement
is I make weekly installments.

05:22.560 --> 05:24.244
You'd know that
if you'd read the contract.

05:24.320 --> 05:25.845
I'm not cutting you a check until Monday.

05:25.920 --> 05:27.968
We need you
to expedite the liquor license.

05:29.480 --> 05:31.164
What makes you think I can do that?

05:31.640 --> 05:33.051
'Cause it's the kind of thing you do.

05:36.040 --> 05:37.201
Let me understand.

05:37.840 --> 05:40.571
You, Mr. By the Book,

05:40.640 --> 05:42.881
are asking me to do something
unscrupulous,

05:42.960 --> 05:45.531
after hating me for living
my unscrupulous life.

05:46.480 --> 05:50.166
I remember when you were 16,
you called me a criminal prick.

05:51.160 --> 05:53.891
Well, look who needs
that criminal prick now.

05:53.960 --> 05:57.248
You need this, too. The restaurant won't
make money if we can't sell wine.

05:57.840 --> 06:00.161
How do you fail to get a liquor license?

06:00.600 --> 06:04.650
Isn't that the whole point
of your, quote, unquote, career?

06:06.080 --> 06:08.128
You're in over your head with this...

06:08.360 --> 06:10.647
clown car you're calling a restaurant.

06:11.680 --> 06:13.808
Either step up to your responsibility

06:14.360 --> 06:16.010
or stop wasting my money.

06:16.080 --> 06:17.081
[coughs]

06:17.480 --> 06:19.562
Can you get us a license or not?

06:20.080 --> 06:21.161
[Sn iffs]

06:23.120 --> 06:24.451
No guarantees.

06:26.200 --> 06:27.326
[coughs]

06:27.400 --> 06:32.201
[mid-tempo guitar plays]

06:33.760 --> 06:39.767
[Aidan coughing, vomits]

06:41.280 --> 06:43.681
[mid-tempo music plays]

06:47.200 --> 06:49.931
♪ Fever dreams ♪

06:50.480 --> 06:53.404
♪ Or so it seems ♪

06:55.400 --> 06:57.209
♪ All I see is ♪

06:57.400 --> 06:59.562
♪ What used to be ♪

06:59.960 --> 07:01.450
♪ Fever dreams ♪

07:02.440 --> 07:05.967
♪ I've been around
I'm lost and found ♪

07:06.080 --> 07:09.527
♪ I burned it all
to the ground ♪

07:10.000 --> 07:13.243
♪ Ashes to ashes
hope that dashes ♪

07:13.600 --> 07:15.807
♪ My own mystery ♪

07:17.120 --> 07:21.842
♪ And all I see
is what used to be ♪

07:28.440 --> 07:30.727
[monitor beeping]

07:33.800 --> 07:35.165
That prison guard?

07:36.280 --> 07:37.441
Taken care of.

07:38.680 --> 07:39.681
[silenced gunshot]

07:40.800 --> 07:42.086
Just like you taught me.

07:44.440 --> 07:47.922
Someone in our organization
leaked my prison visit.

07:49.520 --> 07:52.046
It's the only way the Asians
could have set the hit.

07:54.360 --> 07:57.204
I'll find the rat. Squash it.

08:06.120 --> 08:07.360
Patrick!

08:09.000 --> 08:10.001
How's your father?

08:11.600 --> 08:12.886
No change.

08:12.960 --> 08:14.041
Your sister?

08:14.400 --> 08:15.401
She woke up.

08:16.800 --> 08:18.848
Really? She just...woke up?

08:19.320 --> 08:21.004
It might happen for your father.

08:21.360 --> 08:23.567
He might be back
to his usual self soon.

08:23.640 --> 08:24.721
God willing.

08:25.400 --> 08:26.686
God willing.

08:27.800 --> 08:32.249
Oh, thank you, again,
for your help with the health inspection.

08:32.840 --> 08:34.409
You don't by any chance

08:34.520 --> 08:37.251
know anything about liquor licenses,
do you?

08:37.600 --> 08:38.931
Need to speak with you, Boss.

08:43.200 --> 08:44.246
Well. [chuckles]

08:44.600 --> 08:46.807
I hope this isn't the last time
I get to see you.

08:47.160 --> 08:49.208
You, too. You have my number.

08:51.280 --> 08:53.203
[constricted] Okay.

08:56.960 --> 08:58.849
Her... sister woke up.

08:59.520 --> 09:01.648
Found out who tipped off the Asians.

09:02.520 --> 09:03.931
You're not gonna like it.

09:07.120 --> 09:08.610
Hey. Where you been?

09:08.680 --> 09:09.966
At the hospital.

09:10.040 --> 09:11.690
Let me guess.
You need some money.

09:11.760 --> 09:12.886
Just-- just a scratch, all right?

09:12.960 --> 09:14.724
L-- I got to do some sourcing.

09:15.000 --> 09:17.571
Next installment is Monday.
[door opens]

09:17.840 --> 09:19.888
T.!
No money till Monday?

09:19.960 --> 09:21.769
Come-- come on, man.
What gives?

09:21.840 --> 09:24.366
It's in the contract.
Read it. You'll like it.

09:24.480 --> 09:26.403
Lots of fun surprises in there.

09:26.560 --> 09:28.608
Hey. I'm doing langoustines.

09:29.280 --> 09:30.327
If you could just ask your dad

09:30.400 --> 09:32.004
to give us the installment
just a little early.

09:32.080 --> 09:34.651
Look, I was just at my father's
to ask him to--

09:35.440 --> 09:37.761
for more money, okay,
and we're not gonna get it till Monday.

09:38.120 --> 09:40.407
- T, come on.
- Close the door.

09:44.440 --> 09:46.329
Can't you just go back
and ask him?

09:46.760 --> 09:48.762
The restaurant is not all about you

09:48.840 --> 09:50.604
and your whims, all right?

09:50.720 --> 09:53.007
I've got other issues I'm dealing with.

09:53.520 --> 09:55.363
Dude, look, we still
got to work together here!

09:55.440 --> 09:58.842
Dion. Dion, if there's anyone who can
make something out of nothing,

09:58.960 --> 10:01.008
- it's you.
- [sighs]

10:02.280 --> 10:04.248
[rock music playing]

10:14.280 --> 10:15.327
[chatter]

10:17.920 --> 10:20.127
Hands are, like, impossible.

10:20.360 --> 10:22.010
Easy if they're wearing mittens.

10:22.280 --> 10:24.248
But your hands are awesome, T.J.

10:29.640 --> 10:32.246
I... Googled
what happened to your mom.

10:34.840 --> 10:37.081
Do you r-- remember anything?

10:41.600 --> 10:43.648
- That's messed up.
- [Andre] Hey, turd!

10:44.560 --> 10:45.721
Mute boy.

10:49.640 --> 10:52.962
You know, I think I'm gonna puke
every time I look at your mural.

10:53.040 --> 10:56.203
Well, I need a barf bag
every time I have to look at your face!

10:57.400 --> 10:58.447
[child laughs]

10:58.880 --> 10:59.927
[grunting]

11:00.240 --> 11:02.288
[indistinct shouting]

11:05.320 --> 11:07.129
[groans]

11:09.480 --> 11:10.527
[knock on door]

11:10.720 --> 11:11.767
Sorry to bother you.

11:12.320 --> 11:13.890
Is Dion Patras here?

11:15.040 --> 11:16.804
Dion went to the fish market.

11:17.200 --> 11:18.850
[Pilar] Would you like to wait for him?

11:20.200 --> 11:23.283
- If you'd like to wait...
- No, uh, just--

11:23.760 --> 11:28.800
Have him call me
or meet me there at 3:00 o'clock.

11:32.360 --> 11:33.885
Eastgate Family Clinic?

11:34.440 --> 11:36.727
You do not want to go to
Eastgate Family Clinic.

11:37.800 --> 11:38.767
Why not?

11:39.360 --> 11:40.646
I mean, is there something wrong with it?

11:40.760 --> 11:42.364
Do you have another recommendation?

11:43.840 --> 11:46.320
I recommend
you reconsider your decision.

11:47.720 --> 11:48.881
[scoffs] Excuse me?

11:54.280 --> 11:55.611
How old are you?

11:57.120 --> 11:59.327
I am none-of-your-business years old.

11:59.800 --> 12:01.245
You do not want to do this.

12:01.720 --> 12:04.644
Okay. Look, you don't know
what you're talking about.

12:04.720 --> 12:07.007
Just give Dion the message, please.

12:07.240 --> 12:09.242
I do know what I'm talking about.

12:12.160 --> 12:14.288
Look, there's always a problem.

12:15.720 --> 12:18.166
Matthew gambled away my savings,

12:18.480 --> 12:21.563
Ruben drove my RAV4 into a hotel pool.

12:23.200 --> 12:25.043
I thought Diego was the one,

12:25.640 --> 12:27.529
but he ran off with a stripper.

12:29.760 --> 12:32.240
Two weeks later, I found out I was...

12:35.440 --> 12:38.171
So, it seemed
like the sensible thing to do.

12:39.600 --> 12:40.840
[slow-tempo guitar plays]

12:43.440 --> 12:46.842
Look, I don't know about you and Dion,

12:48.520 --> 12:53.401
but I do know... if you want a baby...

12:55.600 --> 12:58.444
maybe... this is the baby you get.

13:22.600 --> 13:23.601
Yo, what's this?

13:23.920 --> 13:25.046
It's the wire you're gonna wear

13:25.120 --> 13:26.724
next time you meet with the Tooth Fairy.

13:26.800 --> 13:28.643
Oh, hell no. No, no, no, no, no.

13:28.720 --> 13:31.200
Hey. Listen to me.
Are you listening, huh?

13:31.280 --> 13:32.566
I tossed your chef for you.

13:32.800 --> 13:34.848
Okay? It's a two-way street, remember?

13:34.920 --> 13:37.002
- This is what you owe me.
- Come on.

13:37.080 --> 13:39.401
The Tooth Fairy will kill me
if he catches me wearing a wire.

13:39.480 --> 13:42.211
Did you not understand the term
"quid pro quo?"

13:42.280 --> 13:45.170
It's Latin for
you're wearing a goddamn wire.

13:45.600 --> 13:47.602
[panting]

13:51.120 --> 13:52.690
[Dion] Oh, you got to be kidding me.

13:53.720 --> 13:55.370
This belongs in a museum.

13:55.640 --> 13:57.608
The Bluetooth bugs are unreliable.

13:57.920 --> 13:58.967
Like you.

13:59.120 --> 14:01.600
[mid-tempo music plays]

14:07.280 --> 14:08.327
[tires screech]

14:19.080 --> 14:20.320
<i>And voila'.</i>

14:21.360 --> 14:22.885
Poor as a pauper.

14:23.040 --> 14:24.280
Hey, you know what?

14:24.360 --> 14:26.647
Dreams come true to the man who pers--

14:29.760 --> 14:30.886
Hey, Marisa.

14:31.560 --> 14:35.406
Oh, uh, langoustines.
[chuckles]

14:36.000 --> 14:39.641
Yeah, grilled. Salt, pepper,
kiss of lemon. It's, uh, it's beautiful.

14:42.760 --> 14:44.125
She has something to tell you.

14:55.160 --> 14:56.161
[Dion] Wow.

14:56.880 --> 15:00.487
- Okay, uh, I hesitate to ask--
- In the prison visitation room.

15:01.160 --> 15:03.083
When your penis was visiting my vagina.

15:03.240 --> 15:04.287
[scoffs]

15:04.600 --> 15:05.647
Right. Yeah.

15:06.320 --> 15:09.164
- No, I, uh, I still hesitate to ask--
- Yes, Dion.

15:09.240 --> 15:10.287
It's yours.

15:11.400 --> 15:14.529
You were a sparkling oasis
in the desert of my love life.

15:17.440 --> 15:18.930
What do you want to do?

15:21.120 --> 15:22.929
Well, I was thinking about
getting an abortion.

15:25.480 --> 15:28.404
Right. Right.
You know-- you know what?

15:28.480 --> 15:30.369
Wha-- whatever you think is best.

15:30.440 --> 15:32.841
I just want you to know
that I truly, truly support--

15:32.920 --> 15:34.331
I was thinking about it.

15:35.920 --> 15:37.843
Until she changed my mind.

15:40.320 --> 15:41.685
- What?
- [Marisa] I'm sorry.

15:41.760 --> 15:42.841
I don't even know your name.

15:42.960 --> 15:44.121
Oh. Pilar Herrera.
[chuckles]

15:44.200 --> 15:46.168
- Hi. Marisa Gallo.
- [laughs]

15:46.240 --> 15:47.446
Love your earrings, by the way.

15:47.520 --> 15:48.760
- Hoboken Flea Market.
- Oh!

15:49.000 --> 15:50.411
What the hell? What? [stammers]

15:50.480 --> 15:52.721
Pilar opens her mouth
and makes parents of us?

15:52.800 --> 15:53.801
What about what <i>I</i> want?

15:53.880 --> 15:56.201
Okay. Yeah, sure. Let's explore that.

15:56.800 --> 15:59.804
Do you want to be a real father
to a real child

15:59.880 --> 16:01.325
that I am really going to have?

16:03.520 --> 16:04.567
Yeah.

16:05.160 --> 16:06.207
That's what I thought.

16:07.040 --> 16:08.087
Oh, Christ.

16:09.440 --> 16:11.442
This is supposed to be
the happiest day of my life.

16:11.960 --> 16:15.362
What? You were about to have
an abortion like five seconds ago!

16:15.440 --> 16:17.681
Yeah, that's because I knew
that you would react this way.

16:20.200 --> 16:22.680
Oh, you... You.

16:25.600 --> 16:27.409
- Who was that?
- Yeah, my lawyer.

16:28.080 --> 16:29.923
And the mother of his child.

16:32.400 --> 16:34.050
Found your phone in the wine room.

16:34.240 --> 16:35.526
Missed a few calls.

16:35.760 --> 16:37.364
[sighs] Thanks, Mose.

16:47.880 --> 16:49.484
You got your lawyer pregnant?

16:49.840 --> 16:50.887
How did that happen?

16:51.000 --> 16:52.240
You know, the usual way.

16:52.640 --> 16:54.881
Technically, she's not my lawyer anymore.

16:55.000 --> 16:57.401
Oh, a technicality. That's-- that's good.

16:58.600 --> 16:59.567
Seriously?

16:59.760 --> 17:02.604
Your reaction to getting someone pregnant
is to snort cocaine?

17:02.680 --> 17:03.727
[Sniffs]

17:05.480 --> 17:08.086
Yeah, well, I'm fresh out
of celebratory cigars.

17:19.480 --> 17:20.845
[inhales] What's up?

17:21.960 --> 17:24.122
- You must be looking for Tommy.
- Mm-hmm.

17:24.200 --> 17:26.646
He's in the, urn, walk-in.

17:27.520 --> 17:28.681
Thanks.

17:32.200 --> 17:33.929
Do you want a--
Do you want a restaurant or not--

17:34.040 --> 17:36.122
Hi, Mr. Moran. It's Anna Davis.

17:36.240 --> 17:37.207
We have to talk.

17:37.280 --> 17:38.884
Okay, I'll-- I'll be right out.

17:41.480 --> 17:42.641
Dude!

17:45.840 --> 17:47.410
You brought T.J. home.

17:48.800 --> 17:49.961
Why did that happen?

17:50.400 --> 17:52.880
Uh, I called you multiple times.

17:52.960 --> 17:54.803
I'm sorry.
I didn't have my phone on me.

17:55.360 --> 17:58.045
Oh, good. If I could talk to you
and your Support Person together.

17:58.120 --> 17:59.360
[Fiasco] Yo, Chef.

18:00.720 --> 18:02.165
You want these in the walk-in?

18:02.240 --> 18:03.571
[slow-tempo guitar plays]

18:03.720 --> 18:04.767
Sure.

18:10.560 --> 18:14.360
You know,
I'm a <i>support-ive</i> person

18:14.440 --> 18:16.090
if not an actual Support Person.

18:17.800 --> 18:18.847
What's this about?

18:19.800 --> 18:21.211
Can I talk to you privately?

18:21.640 --> 18:24.883
Yeah.
Urn, why don't you go help Habib

18:24.960 --> 18:27.042
while I talk to Ms. Davis, okay, pal?

18:28.200 --> 18:29.281
Right here.

18:34.120 --> 18:37.169
Uh, T.J. got into a serious fight at
school

18:37.520 --> 18:38.965
a fight that he started.

18:39.440 --> 18:40.441
What?

18:40.960 --> 18:42.803
Your son will be suspended for two days.

18:42.960 --> 18:44.803
No-- Jesus.

18:44.880 --> 18:46.120
You know, Mr. Moran,

18:46.200 --> 18:49.329
I'm receiving a lot of pressure
to bring in Child Services.

18:50.000 --> 18:51.490
Wha-- Pressure from who?

18:52.520 --> 18:54.841
The principal, the administration.

18:56.120 --> 18:57.645
T.J. hasn't spoken in a year.

18:57.840 --> 18:59.683
- [scoffs]
- His grades are failing.

18:59.880 --> 19:01.644
And now he's violent in school.

19:02.000 --> 19:05.004
Look, I'm telling you.
He-- he must have been provoked.

19:05.160 --> 19:06.161
[sighs]

19:07.200 --> 19:08.201
You know, I came here today

19:08.280 --> 19:11.727
wondering if I could ease their
concern about T.J.'s situation.

19:11.840 --> 19:13.285
Look at him. Look.

19:14.720 --> 19:16.245
You see how engaged he is?

19:16.680 --> 19:18.330
I mean, surely there are other kids

19:18.400 --> 19:21.324
who are more in need of the
protection of Child Services.

19:21.400 --> 19:23.289
I smelled marijuana when I walked in.

19:23.960 --> 19:25.485
You lied about having a Support Person.

19:25.600 --> 19:27.841
- L-- Look, that was a misunderstanding.
- I'm sorry.

19:27.920 --> 19:29.490
I will be calling Child Services.

19:29.560 --> 19:30.607
Why? Why would--

19:30.720 --> 19:32.688
They'll make a visit, unannounced

19:32.760 --> 19:35.161
to see if this is
a suitable environment for T.J.

19:35.240 --> 19:36.446
That's totally unnecessary.

19:36.520 --> 19:37.567
Well, I'm doing you a favor.

19:37.640 --> 19:39.369
I could lose my job
if they found out I gave you

19:39.440 --> 19:41.010
- a heads up about this visit.
- Yeah, maybe you should lose your job.

19:42.040 --> 19:43.041
[scoffs]

19:44.000 --> 19:47.209
For your son's sake,
Mr. Moran, get your shit together.

19:51.040 --> 19:52.849
[Billy] That looks amazing, Boss.

19:52.960 --> 19:54.246
Oh, by the way...

19:55.440 --> 19:56.965
here's a list of the safe houses

19:57.040 --> 19:59.611
we've been checking out
in case we got to move product.

19:59.880 --> 20:02.770
You cook a mean rabbit.
Magnifique. Yeah.

20:02.840 --> 20:04.126
Real good meal, Boss.

20:04.200 --> 20:05.929
Would you make me a cappuccino, please?

20:06.840 --> 20:08.046
Mm.

20:08.920 --> 20:09.967
Dessert wine?

20:11.320 --> 20:14.290
- Thank you.
- Any word on who told the Asians

20:14.600 --> 20:17.001
when I was going to be
visiting my father in prison?

20:17.320 --> 20:19.084
We'll catch the rat. Don't worry.

20:21.080 --> 20:22.411
How's the crème brûlée?

20:22.600 --> 20:23.840
To die for.

20:27.240 --> 20:28.605
What are you doing with all that money?

20:30.760 --> 20:32.649
What? What money?

20:36.920 --> 20:38.126
[dramatic music plays]

20:39.520 --> 20:40.567
I'm joking.

20:40.640 --> 20:42.529
[Woichik laughs] Jesus.

20:43.280 --> 20:44.725
You're my cousin.

20:45.960 --> 20:47.121
<i>Nostrovia.</i>

20:48.360 --> 20:49.566
<i>Nostrovia.</i>

20:50.400 --> 20:51.561
[chuckles]

20:54.360 --> 20:57.250
If I thought it was you, you'd know.

21:00.160 --> 21:02.925
- [gagging]
- And now you know.

21:11.480 --> 21:12.845
Can you hear me, Billy?

21:15.920 --> 21:16.921
Good.

21:17.080 --> 21:18.570
'Cause I want you to hear this.

21:19.360 --> 21:20.407
[grunts]

21:21.360 --> 21:24.091
I am going to watch you die.

21:27.040 --> 21:30.840
Actually, Patricia, you can expedite
a liquor license for a friend.

21:31.720 --> 21:33.609
A friend who helped your husband
cut some corners

21:33.680 --> 21:35.364
to get his condos built.

21:37.840 --> 21:39.490
I know you'll do your best.

21:41.080 --> 21:43.128
[telephone beeps]
What a bitch.

21:43.880 --> 21:44.961
[sighs]

21:45.360 --> 21:46.521
You were saying?

21:47.680 --> 21:50.570
The abdominal pain,
shortness of breath, vomiting,

21:51.360 --> 21:52.805
platelet count is down.

21:53.600 --> 21:56.331
White-cell count is not good.

21:56.720 --> 21:57.721
I thought your treatment

21:57.800 --> 22:00.406
was supposed to do something
other than make me more sick.

22:00.480 --> 22:02.721
Relapse was always a possibility.

22:03.000 --> 22:04.047
Hmm.

22:04.880 --> 22:06.006
Bottom line?

22:07.800 --> 22:09.529
You need a bone-marrow transplant.

22:09.640 --> 22:11.005
And if I don't want to do that?

22:11.720 --> 22:13.210
At this stage of leukemia,

22:13.320 --> 22:16.051
the prognosis can be less than a year.

22:19.080 --> 22:22.801
Have you discussed your health condition
with your family?

22:24.280 --> 22:26.487
Blood relatives are your best bet

22:26.720 --> 22:29.007
as far as finding a matching donor.

22:32.800 --> 22:35.804
[slow-tempo guitar plays]

23:10.000 --> 23:11.286
What are you doing here?

23:12.160 --> 23:13.685
Well, it's her birthday.

23:16.400 --> 23:18.767
Hey, I knew her before you did, bro.

23:24.400 --> 23:28.291
Uh, remember that one Halloween
at the Webster Avenue apartment?

23:29.080 --> 23:30.127
Yeah.

23:35.720 --> 23:38.246
Right.
It's-- It's probably not appropriate.

23:38.440 --> 23:39.566
Probably not.

23:42.680 --> 23:43.727
Yeah.

23:51.360 --> 23:53.044
[sighs]

24:02.840 --> 24:05.241
<i>♪ ...birthday to you X</i>

24:05.880 --> 24:10.568
♪ Happy birthday dear Rie ♪

24:10.640 --> 24:11.721
[laughter]

24:11.880 --> 24:16.408
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

24:16.480 --> 24:18.005
[cheering]
[drumming on table]

24:18.080 --> 24:19.525
- [Dion] Oooh!
- Oh!

24:20.800 --> 24:22.131
Oh! Whoo!

24:22.480 --> 24:23.481
What did you wish for?

24:23.560 --> 24:25.847
Well, it won't come true
if I say it out loud.

24:26.520 --> 24:28.602
[T.J.] Well, you should have wished
for more wishes.

24:28.680 --> 24:29.681
Oh.

24:29.760 --> 24:31.364
Then you could tell me
what you wished for,

24:31.440 --> 24:32.965
and if it didn't come true,

24:33.080 --> 24:35.208
you'd still have like 1,000 more wishes.

24:35.280 --> 24:36.406
Kid has a point.

24:36.480 --> 24:38.608
But if I told you
I wished for more wishes,

24:38.680 --> 24:41.331
then the wish for more wishes
wouldn't happen. See?

24:41.760 --> 24:42.966
- [Dion chuckles]
- That's not how it works.

24:43.040 --> 24:44.246
[Dion] Yeah, Rie, that's not how it works.

24:44.320 --> 24:45.446
Of course not.
But you know what?

24:45.520 --> 24:46.567
I'm curious, too.

24:46.960 --> 24:48.530
Yeah, come on.
Don't keep it to yourself.

24:50.080 --> 24:51.684
Okay. Okay.

24:52.600 --> 24:55.524
I wished for a perfect
opening night at Thirio,

24:55.800 --> 25:01.045
in the not-too-distant future,
with my boys.

25:02.200 --> 25:04.328
- And a pony.
- [Dion chuckles]

25:04.440 --> 25:06.681
Really holding out
for a pony this year, guys.

25:06.800 --> 25:07.847
[cellphone vibrates]

25:08.040 --> 25:09.849
Ah, man. Listen, I got to jet.

25:09.920 --> 25:11.160
I love you and leave you.

25:11.280 --> 25:13.931
- Happy birthday, old lady
- Old lady?

25:14.000 --> 25:15.081
[Dion chuckles]

25:17.200 --> 25:18.850
There.
Get the first piece.

25:19.640 --> 25:22.120
[slow-tempo guitar plays]

25:56.280 --> 25:58.442
[mid-tempo music plays]

26:00.560 --> 26:01.721
[pan sizzling]

26:05.240 --> 26:07.163
- Fire in the hole!
- [Fiasco] There we go.

26:08.320 --> 26:09.321
Whoo!

26:19.480 --> 26:20.481
[cellphone rings]

26:25.240 --> 26:26.366
Uh, excuse me.

26:28.960 --> 26:30.086
Hello?

26:30.160 --> 26:32.162
I need to see you.
My house.

26:33.120 --> 26:35.646
Look, I can't, man.
I-- I'm in the middle of cooking.

26:35.920 --> 26:38.002
Cooking for your friend, Tommy Moran?

26:38.120 --> 26:40.691
And his angelic son, T.J.?

26:41.160 --> 26:43.162
How about that lovely
lawyer friend of yours?

26:43.240 --> 26:45.288
What's her name? Marisa Gallo?

26:46.200 --> 26:47.611
She seems nice.

26:50.360 --> 26:52.124
I'm not asking, Dion.

26:56.640 --> 26:57.641
[sighs]

27:06.920 --> 27:09.526
That's not how I showed you.
Why are you going so easy?

27:23.640 --> 27:24.926
Did you get into a fight?

27:28.200 --> 27:29.770
Did you win?

27:33.000 --> 27:34.047
[chuckles]

27:34.680 --> 27:35.727
Attaboy.

27:36.160 --> 27:37.207
[chuckles]

27:38.960 --> 27:40.485
Let's give your knuckles time to heal.

27:41.280 --> 27:42.884
I want to show you something new.

27:47.360 --> 27:48.566
There you are.

27:50.280 --> 27:52.089
I got a call back from that PR lady.

27:52.960 --> 27:55.281
Thirio's gonna have some buzz
for opening night.

27:55.800 --> 27:57.006
Buzz is good.

28:00.520 --> 28:01.885
We missed you at Grief Group.

28:03.680 --> 28:05.205
I couldn't drive.

28:05.920 --> 28:07.524
I would have given you a ride.

28:07.800 --> 28:10.406
I didn't want to go, you know?

28:11.760 --> 28:15.242
The last thing I need
is our Crying Circle of Fun,

28:16.200 --> 28:19.204
sitting around,
talking about how sad we all are.

28:20.520 --> 28:22.761
I'm not sad. I'm pissed.

28:24.360 --> 28:25.486
I'm angry.

28:26.720 --> 28:31.009
Left this stinking hole
in my life for no good reason.

28:31.720 --> 28:32.801
[Fiasco] I hear you, man.

28:32.880 --> 28:36.646
My ex, Tiffany? She didn't die.

28:37.160 --> 28:38.366
She left me.

28:38.720 --> 28:43.601
But it's like-- no explanation,
no note, no nothing.

28:43.880 --> 28:46.531
Sometimes it crushes my heart so bad,
I can't breathe.

28:47.120 --> 28:48.770
Plus, bitch stole my PlayStation.

28:49.800 --> 28:53.043
Uh... this is a little different.

28:53.440 --> 28:54.441
Okay.

28:56.080 --> 28:57.081
It's my bad.

29:01.920 --> 29:05.527
You know,
I put on this face for T.J. every day,

29:06.240 --> 29:10.325
and sometimes, I just can't.
I-- I can't keep lying.

29:10.800 --> 29:11.847
Lying?

29:12.200 --> 29:14.646
Yeah. All the shit I tell him.

29:15.440 --> 29:16.965
"She's in a better place."

29:17.560 --> 29:19.642
What am I supposed to teach him
about a world that...

29:20.800 --> 29:23.406
that takes
a mother from her son like that?

29:23.480 --> 29:24.606
What do I say to him?

29:26.000 --> 29:27.889
That tomorrow will be better.

29:31.840 --> 29:32.841
[scoffs]

29:34.760 --> 29:35.761
How do you do it?

29:38.320 --> 29:39.651
I mean, you lost a husband.

29:39.760 --> 29:41.489
How do you stay so optimistic?

29:48.240 --> 29:49.401
Well, you're right.

29:51.320 --> 29:52.890
Tomorrow will be better.

29:55.360 --> 29:57.522
Cause' it won't be
Rie's birthday anymore.

29:57.800 --> 30:00.087
[mid-tempo guitar plays]

30:20.480 --> 30:22.608
- Detective.
- Counselor.

30:23.560 --> 30:26.404
Donna cut me way too big a slice
of cherry crumble.

30:26.480 --> 30:28.482
- Have some.
- Not hungry.

30:30.960 --> 30:33.327
You here to bust my chops
about Patrick Woichik?

30:33.680 --> 30:34.886
Give it a rest, will you?

30:37.960 --> 30:39.007
[sighs]

30:39.120 --> 30:40.485
You're gonna be a grandpa.

30:47.520 --> 30:50.205
The father's not in the picture, just FYI.

30:53.120 --> 30:54.121
[laughs]

30:58.040 --> 30:59.166
Come here.

30:59.360 --> 31:00.407
[groans]

31:00.800 --> 31:01.881
[laughs]

31:04.000 --> 31:05.047
[sighs]

31:07.120 --> 31:08.360
I haven't told Morn yet.

31:08.560 --> 31:10.483
You want me to tell her, huh?
She'll be happy.

31:10.880 --> 31:12.484
I know.
That's exactly why I got knocked up,

31:12.560 --> 31:14.130
- so Mom would be happy.
- [laughs]

31:14.200 --> 31:16.771
[sighs] Hey, hey. Marisa, listen to me.

31:17.640 --> 31:20.371
You're not doing this alone, okay?
Whatever you need, I'm here for you.

31:20.880 --> 31:22.803
- You got that?
- Yeah.

31:25.360 --> 31:26.805
[cellphone vibrates]
Ooh.

31:26.880 --> 31:27.961
Sorry, honey.

31:31.320 --> 31:32.321
I got to go.

31:32.560 --> 31:34.005
I am so happy for you.

31:35.400 --> 31:36.526
Where you going?

31:36.680 --> 31:39.126
I have work. One of my cases blew up.

31:40.040 --> 31:41.087
Dad.

31:42.520 --> 31:45.444
Whatever you're doing,
be careful, all right?

31:46.840 --> 31:47.921
Serious.

31:50.360 --> 31:51.441
I need you.

31:52.520 --> 31:53.965
Don't worry about me, pumpkin.

31:54.040 --> 31:56.850
Hey. Get yourself some dinner, okay?

31:57.480 --> 31:58.845
Something besides pie.

32:02.200 --> 32:03.645
Remember how I showed you.

32:04.200 --> 32:06.407
This is not a toy.
This is a weapon. Understand?

32:14.480 --> 32:15.811
Okay, relax.

32:16.040 --> 32:17.087
Aim.

32:18.720 --> 32:20.051
Finger on the trigger.

32:21.760 --> 32:23.285
A gentle squeeze.

32:27.000 --> 32:29.241
Wow. Let's try something
with a little less kick.

32:29.320 --> 32:30.481
Might be easier to handle.

32:30.600 --> 32:32.967
Jensen, give me
that pearl-handled revolver.

32:42.680 --> 32:43.727
Not bad.

32:43.960 --> 32:45.769
[slow-tempo guitar plays]

33:10.000 --> 33:13.004
[knock on door]

33:14.720 --> 33:15.721
[Static]

33:23.320 --> 33:25.288
[scoffs] Damn.

33:25.560 --> 33:28.006
Come. I need your expertise.

33:29.680 --> 33:33.651
I tasted the most sublime Coq Au Riesling
in a little village in Alsace.

33:34.640 --> 33:36.847
The chef was kind enough
to give me his recipe.

33:37.360 --> 33:39.806
I followed his instructions to the letter,

33:39.880 --> 33:44.329
but it's still missing...
a little... je ne sais quoi.

33:46.760 --> 33:49.047
You call me here
to taste your Coq Au Riesling?

33:49.400 --> 33:50.561
I trust your judgment.

34:00.880 --> 34:02.041
Oh, it's good. Yeah.

34:02.120 --> 34:04.964
It's, uh, restaurant-quality.

34:05.760 --> 34:06.761
And?

34:08.040 --> 34:10.884
Well, it could be the greatest
Coq Au Riesling in the world,

34:11.400 --> 34:14.005
but then anyone in the world could make it
'cause I'm tasting the recipe.

34:14.080 --> 34:16.242
Now,
I-- I'm not tasting you.

34:16.320 --> 34:17.650
What do you think it needs?

34:17.880 --> 34:19.563
Well, what do you think it needs?

34:20.199 --> 34:21.326
You're the chef.

34:21.400 --> 34:24.324
Perhaps a little... crème fraîche-.

34:25.280 --> 34:26.281
There you go.

34:26.360 --> 34:27.600
There's some in the fridge.

34:28.600 --> 34:31.126
Hey, you know, Patrick, look.
I could talk food all day,

34:31.199 --> 34:33.123
I really could,
but you know, I'm kind of b--

34:33.679 --> 34:34.886
[dramatic music plays]

34:35.159 --> 34:36.161
Oh.

34:36.880 --> 34:38.005
<i>Oh, Jesus.</i>

34:40.159 --> 34:42.288
This is what happens
when people betray me.

35:07.800 --> 35:09.370
Do you trust me, Dion?

35:10.520 --> 35:11.521
Yeah, I do.

35:24.920 --> 35:26.046
I didn't get anything.

35:26.120 --> 35:27.645
What the hell happened to my wire?

35:28.960 --> 35:31.930
[rock music plays]

35:32.000 --> 35:33.490
I'm not working for you anymore.

35:33.560 --> 35:35.483
You're in for a world of hurt
you quit on me.

35:35.560 --> 35:36.561
You know what I can do to you?

35:36.640 --> 35:37.687
What can you do?

35:37.880 --> 35:39.120
Come on. Do it. I don't give a shit.

35:39.280 --> 35:41.282
'Cause what he could do
is 1,000 times worse

35:41.360 --> 35:42.964
than anything you could imagine.

35:44.520 --> 35:45.851
[sighs]

35:50.320 --> 35:51.606
[sighs] Thanks, Jensen.

35:53.280 --> 35:54.327
[sniffles]

35:54.440 --> 35:56.283
Teej, come here.

35:58.880 --> 35:59.881
Listen, buddy.

35:59.960 --> 36:03.169
We got to talk about what
happened at school, the fight?

36:04.520 --> 36:07.000
Teej. Hey. Don't ignore me.

36:07.200 --> 36:08.281
Hey.

36:09.400 --> 36:10.401
T.J.

36:12.040 --> 36:14.964
How'd that fight happen, huh?
Did you-- did you start it?

36:16.800 --> 36:20.088
Teej. What are you doing, huh?
We're-- we're about to have dinner.

36:20.760 --> 36:22.000
DON'T“ hey!

36:22.080 --> 36:25.289
No sandwich right now, okay?
Don't-- hey. Don't ignore me.

36:25.560 --> 36:27.289
Come on. You know what?
Let's go upstairs.

36:27.760 --> 36:30.366
Let's go-- hey!
Let's-- Teej. Hey!

36:30.440 --> 36:31.680
God damn it!

36:32.360 --> 36:33.361
Talk to me!

36:34.320 --> 36:35.446
Talk to me!

36:35.880 --> 36:38.724
I can't help you unless
you say something, god damn it!

36:46.640 --> 36:48.244
[sighs]

36:55.400 --> 36:57.721
I don't want to be this angry
all the time.

36:58.800 --> 37:01.531
You're not angry at T.J.
because he can't talk.

37:06.720 --> 37:08.245
You're angry at Rie...

37:10.520 --> 37:11.931
because she can't talk.

37:13.360 --> 37:14.566
I am.

37:17.280 --> 37:18.691
Look,uh“.

37:21.280 --> 37:23.521
I know I must be a...

37:23.600 --> 37:25.841
piss-poor consolation prize.

37:28.160 --> 37:29.969
Yeah, I'm not going anywhere.

37:31.320 --> 37:32.446
[Dion] You got me.

37:35.800 --> 37:37.006
I love you, man.

37:40.040 --> 37:41.041
Thanks.

37:48.240 --> 37:49.241
Really? Thanks?

37:49.320 --> 37:50.606
I mean,
I-- I just said, "I love you,"

37:50.680 --> 37:52.125
and all you can say is, "Thanks?"

37:53.320 --> 37:54.367
[laughs]

37:56.640 --> 37:57.971
I love you, too, Dion.

37:58.040 --> 37:59.929
It doesn't count
if I have to pry it out of you.

38:00.000 --> 38:01.161
Oh, for God's sake.

38:05.760 --> 38:07.250
I really love you.

38:07.320 --> 38:08.321
I mean...

38:10.160 --> 38:13.084
- I-- a love that I've never--
- [cellphone vibrates]

38:15.120 --> 38:16.167
[Tommy sniffles]

38:17.960 --> 38:20.725
[sighs heavily]

38:20.800 --> 38:21.847
What?

38:22.160 --> 38:23.525
We got our liquor license.

38:24.400 --> 38:25.401
What-- what do you mean?

38:25.480 --> 38:27.244
I th-- thought we already had
our liquor license.

38:28.560 --> 38:29.607
Don't worry about it.

38:34.800 --> 38:37.485
Listen, you got to get rid of any coke

38:37.560 --> 38:41.565
you may or may not have
lying around, all right?

